			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Another thing that helps in role-playing is to <BR>
come up with an interesting story. It has already <BR>
been suggested to come up with a history. What I<BR>
am recommending is that you make that history a<BR>
true hi-story! Make it juicy! Something that other<BR>
players will want to listen to and interact with.<BR>
<BR>
Another suggestion would be to come up with what<BR>
writers call, unique beats. These are unique <BR>
things that your character does when not speaking.<BR>
For example, Glick, the Lick is a healer. So he <BR>
likes to &quot;lick&quot; the boo boos (he's an ogre, what <BR>
can I say). These interactive beats then help <BR>
initiate role-playing!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
